    {
      "id": "93",
      "name": "Lore",
      "components": [
        {
          "component_id": "customize",
          "data": {
            "data": {
              "parsed_content": [
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 255, 255)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Decarabian",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "level": 1,
                  "type": "heading"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "3000 years ago, Old Mondstadt (now Stormterror's Lair) was ruled by Decarabian, the God of Storms. There was a war between the Lord of the Tower, Decarabian, and the King of the North Wind, Andrius. It was a time when Mondstadt was a frozen wasteland, and nothing could survive outside the Old Mondstadt. Tired of the attacks of the God Andrius, Decarabian built a wall of storms around his capital, so that the King of the North Wind could not break through. Decarabian believed that he protected his people and that the people worshiped him out of love, but in reality, they lived in tyranny, restrictions, and fear. Each resident of the city was assigned their own role; songs and music were forbidden; and people’s backs did not straighten due to the raging winds.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/02/20/237301566/25feb67d533079a8733817a551575202_7165222132722080366.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "One day, about 2,600 years ago, people could not withstand the tyranny of the Lord of the Tower anymore, and an uprising began, started by the Nameless Bard; Decarabian's former beloved, Amos; Gunnhildr, the daughter of the clan chief; a red-haired warrior; and an Anemo spirit. The tyrant was defeated by Amos's arrow, Amos herself and the Nameless Bard fell in battle, and the spirit absorbed the powers of the deceased Archon and became the new Anemo Archon Barbatos, taking on the appearance of the Nameless Bard. Gunnhildr was the one who decorated the victorious Anemo Archon with laurels.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 215, 128)"
                      ],
